-- China Stocks: Chalco, Shanghai Chaori Solar, United Electronics
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2011-12-20T08:33:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-20/china-stocks-chalco-shanghai-chaori-solar-united-electronics.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual (SHSZ300)  moves in  China  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close.  The  Shanghai Composite Index (SHCOMP) , which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, fell 2.31 points, or 0.1 percent, to
2,215.93. The CSI 300 Index declined 0.3 percent to 2,377.07.  Aluminum Corp. of China Ltd. (601600)  (601600 CH), the listed unit
of nation’s biggest maker of the lightweight metal and also
called Chalco, slid 0.6 percent to 6.57 yuan. Shenyin & Wanguo
Securities Co. lowered Chalco’s earnings per-share forecast for
this year by 38 percent to 0.05 yuan and for 2012 by 18 percent
to 0.18 yuan, citing capacity expansion and rising costs from
increases in power rates, Ye Peipei, Guo Peng and Xu Ruoxu,
analysts at the Shanghai-based brokerage, said in a report today.  Shanghai Chaori Solar Energy Science & Technology Co. (002506) 
(002506 CH) advanced 4.4 percent to 15.57 yuan, its highest
close since Dec. 1. The company will supply 60 megawatts of
solar modules to  Japan  next year for $75 million, Chaori said in
a statement today.  United Electronics Co.  (002642 CH) rose 16 percent from its
offer price to 28.97 yuan on its first day of trading in
Shenzhen.  --Zhang Shidong. Editor: Shiyin Chen  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
